\newlabel{tab:ablation}{{III}{4}{Single-split KD sensitivity analysis for the resnet50 teacher (fold 0 of the Cassava cross-validation split). Temperature is swept at $\alpha =0.7$ and $\alpha $ at $T=4$; $^{\dagger }$ marks the default used in the main study. Precision, recall, and F1 are macro-averaged. Values are single-split point estimates (no fold error bars)}{table.3}{}}
\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {IV}{\ignorespaces Post-training quantization of the distilled MobileNetV3-Small on the Cassava single-split test set. Precision, recall, and F1 are macro-averaged. Static rows use PT2E reference quantization, whose simulated graph makes serialized size unrepresentative of a deployed int8 model ($-$). Chance is $20\%$ and the majority-class rate is $62\%$. The static int8 accuracies are single draws at a fixed calibration seed and carry roughly $\pm 8$ points of calibration noise (Section~\ref {sec:quant}); only their common verdict --- collapse --- is robust.}}{4}{table.4}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:quant}{{IV}{4}{Post-training quantization of the distilled MobileNetV3-Small on the Cassava single-split test set. Precision, recall, and F1 are macro-averaged. Static rows use PT2E reference quantization, whose simulated graph makes serialized size unrepresentative of a deployed int8 model ($-$). Chance is $20\%$ and the majority-class rate is $62\%$. The static int8 accuracies are single draws at a fixed calibration seed and carry roughly $\pm 8$ points of calibration noise (Section~\ref {sec:quant}); only their common verdict --- collapse --- is robust}{table.4}{}}
